caption:
Urgent Update: Critical Fees Needed to Save My Twin Nieces

Dear friends and family,

Thank you so much for the love, support, and generosity you’ve shown on this journey to bring my twin nieces home. Your help has meant everything to us.

We’ve hit a critical moment in the adoption process, and I need your support more than ever. To move forward and ensure my nieces don’t remain in foster care, I must pay the following fees as soon as possible:
 1. Adoption Fees (Part 2): $2,000 is due soon, with a remaining balance of $6,394.
 2. Legal Fees (South African Attorney): $3,064 is also due immediately for the legal processing of our dossier.

That’s a total of $5,064 needed upfront to continue this process. While the remaining balance may be eligible for a payment plan, I’m praying that we secure a grant by then to reduce the financial strain.

Here’s the amazing part: if 253 people donated just $20 each, we’d reach this goal and take the next step to bring my nieces home. That’s all it would take!

These fees are urgent and must be paid to prevent delays in the process. Time is NOT on our side, and every moment they remain in foster care weighs heavily on my heart.

PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE, if you can donate, share this campaign, or connect us with someone who can help, it would mean the world to me and to these two little girls who desperately need a safe and loving home.

Every single dollar and share gets us closer to reuniting as a family. We don’t know many people and trying to spread the word has not been easy. We are truly counting on the help  and kindness of everyone like you.

Thank you from the bottom of my heart for standing with us during this critical time.

With urgency and gratitude,
Jo-Anne & Rafael

caption:
Sometimes the world f*s with us and it’s just our journey. 

As a courtesy to clients in knowing the power of Astrology, I always share with them their natal chart so as I always say, you may soon see all you are meant to Be ✨ 

Meet Blaire. Fellow @skynyrd lover & mirror image of my natal chart. Literally. Every sign placement mirror image. Every degree. All of it. I’ve queried multiple Astrologists into this anomaly because after all, I’ve never seen a thing like it in my years of holding space for reiki clients. 

My husband met Blaire via @centralserviceli as she was a single mom recently out of an abusive relationship she fled cross country to escape. Living temporarily with local family, along with her physically disabled son, they soon lost housing altogether…the whole family. Fast forward a few years and Blaire and her son Leo have become part of our family and we’ve been doing all we can to help but given we live in a shoe box in one of the most expensive counties in the country, the best we can do right now is spread the word. She and her son, Leo are safely housed in a shelter at present and Blaire has ALWAYS kept down jobs and done by the book, per Department of Social Services and is now awaiting her next appointment to find out about housing but can’t do it without monetary assistance. At this time DSS says due to her making too much income they cannot provide immediate assistance. 

Blaire has spent days crying in shame for even posting a Go Fund Me. What I told her? Till they’re in your shoes… Speak. Your. Truth. 

This woman is a survivor. A warrior. A Goddess. I’ve seen her Goddess potential since the get go and her darkest nights of the soul and we are here to support.  If you find it in your pockets to Be able to do so this holiday season? Then by all means, you are quite a beautiful soul even moreso in acts of service as this and I can assure you, her gratitude eternal and every cent going toward her son and cost of living. 

Thank you for reading. 🙏🤍
*Direct link in stories & my website. 

The 2023 tats? A great f*in year despite the blows of the 3D.

caption:
In nature, nothing is perfect and everything is perfect. Trees can be contorted, bent in weird ways, and they’re still beautiful. –Alice Walker

When we go to nature we accept all its variations and unique shapes and forms as beautiful. A nature lover marvels, respects, accepts, enjoys, appreciates and sees the beauty in nature - recognizing everything spawned from a seed of life and since has been on an epic journey of growth and change. We accept nature that has been molded to what it is with every rock, tree and land has experienced change through the carving hands of time. 

Finding beauty in “imperfections”, or rather variations, is to accept nature in all its forms for what it is, rather than consumed over what needs to change. We don’t ponder how much better a tree would look if it was more straighter, thinner or thicker, darker or lighter, because we find it beautiful just as it is. We accept nature’s imperfect journey as perfect and beautiful. It’s too bad we can’t see the same in ourselves. 

Last year my photographer friend Tommy Corey took this photo of me for his book-in-progress, featuring 100 humans with varying bodies and stories in beautiful nature portraiture — each accompanied with a personal story including how and why nature has called them into its home. 

Tommy and I met in 2021 (swipe left) when he asked to film my story in the desert (a favorite) for a short film series he was creating on different kinds of people and their connection to outside. We had fun filming. Our playfully crass personalities aligned, we became friends, and I’m excited to be a part of another Tommy project. 💚

Tommy and I are both releasing our debut books next summer: My book being the “Monster and Me” picture book inspired by my rare disease, disability & journey to acceptance, and Tommy’s portrait photo book of 100 humans outdoors! I hope you will support both of these projects-of-love in the summer of 2025! #Kamswheelstravel

You may ask yourself what on earth is a white woman from Long Island, New York always preaching about Jamaica? The country that is my homeland for all the sakes of manhood. In divine teachings, we dare say like Jesus the Christ that God is within you. Me is here to tell you this truth of prophecy and legend that is true for all mankind within and without and above and below. To know the truth of nature and the stars and moon to know the cosmos like the back of your hand to know the freedoms that come in speaking your truths. For all emancipation and wonder comes from within when we channel the highest above without fear or judgement for what will come or be for that is the idea of all humanity. 

✨✨✨

I channel musicians and only way I can describe their messages is that my fingers take over. Call me crazy. Unfollow. Cancel me. I know who the f* I Am in this life and I Am Alli Anderson. Wife, Mom, Nurse, Reiki Master & Psychic Intuitive here trying to figure out every moment just like you. I am for all intents and purposes just a white chick from Long Island with a crazy ass connection to Jamaica. We’ve been 6 times. I’ve healed there. I’ve transformed. I’ve been liberated there from my darkest nights of the soul. I am for all intents and purposes One Love 🇯🇲 🌎✌️ Ya Mon. 

PS- for healing purposes, utilizing native Jamaican herbs as Soursop and Cerasee can help ease such issues as neurological and GI. I drank this combo along with turmeric and black pepper daily for months and it brought me so much healing. I don’t advise cerasee in sips- just shoot it. It’s worse than wormwood!!! 🤢😂

Have a high vibe weekend, beautiful souls. Pics are recaps from our trip. Was hoping to visit home and resting place of the man, the legend himself @bobmarley, but we couldn’t get there. One day I hope to share in the love and beauty that is your truth. Respect. One love. Always xo, Alli
